<script type="text/javascript">
  jQuery(document).ready(function(){
    jQuery('#li_tab_1').addClass('selected');
  });
  function show_tab(div){
    if (div == 'web'){
      jQuery('.selected').removeClass();
      jQuery('#li_tab_1').addClass('selected');
      jQuery('#web').show();
      jQuery('#mob').hide();
      jQuery('#tw').hide();
      jQuery('#fb').hide();
    }
    else if (div == 'mob'){
      jQuery('.selected').removeClass();
      jQuery('#li_tab_2').addClass('selected');
      jQuery('#web').hide();
      jQuery('#mob').show();
      jQuery('#tw').hide();
      jQuery('#fb').hide();
    }
    else if (div == 'tw'){
      jQuery('.selected').removeClass();
      jQuery('#li_tab_3').addClass('selected');
      jQuery('#web').hide();
      jQuery('#mob').hide();
      jQuery('#tw').show();
      jQuery('#fb').hide();
    }
    else{
      jQuery('.selected').removeClass();
      jQuery('#li_tab_4').addClass('selected');
      jQuery('#web').hide();
      jQuery('#mob').hide();
      jQuery('#tw').hide();
      jQuery('#fb').show();
    }
  }
</script>
<div id="pagewidth">
  <div id="content">
    <div >
      <ul class="tabNavigation tabs-block" style="width:auto !important; margin-left: 37%;">
        <li id="li_tab_1"><a href="#" onclick="show_tab('web')">Website</a></li>
        <li id="li_tab_2"><a href="#" onclick="show_tab('mob')">Mobile</a></li>
        
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="row grey">
      <div class="center howitworks" style="text-align:center;">
        <div id="web">
          <h1>Start Website Campaigns in 3 Easy Steps</h1>
          <div class="gallery">
            <ul style="text-align:center">
              <li> <span class="setupcamp"></span>
                <h3>Add your Website</h3>
              </li>
              <li> <span class="integratecamp"></span>
                <h3>Integrate JS Code</h3>
              </li>
              <li> <span class="deploycamp"></span>
                <h3>Launch & Analyze</h3>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="columns">
            <div class="step"><span class="step_1"></span>
              <p>Set up your Website by simply providing your domain name and campaigns like Feedback, Notification or, Coupon using a WYSIWIG editor. You can then control whom to show your campaign based on user behavior, site url, time spent on page, repeat vs new user and lot more. </p>
            </div>
            <div class="step"><span class="step_2"></span>
              <p>Include our one line Javascript code in your website's footer once. That's all. Once it is setup, you can start/stop any number of campaigns at any given time without changing any additional line of code ever.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="step"><span class="step_3"></span>
              <p>Just click Launch and camppaigns like Feedback, Notification or, Coupon will start to show for all your users instantly. You will also start to see near real-time reports of users' interaction with your campaigns - views/clicks/leads etc.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div><!-- id="web"   -->

        <div id="mob" style="display:none;">
          <h1>Run In App Campaigns to increase Downloads & Sales</h1>
          <div class="gallery">
            <ul style="text-align:center">
              <li> <span class="setupcamp"></span>
                <h3>Add your Mobile App</h3>
              </li>
              <li> <span class="integratecamp" style="background-position: 21px -125px !important;"></span>
                <h3>Download & Integrate SDK</h3>
              </li>
              <li> <span class="deploycamp" style="background-position: 10px -762px !important;"></span>
                <h3>Launch & Analyze</h3>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="columns">
            <div class="step"><span class="step_1"></span>
              <p>Set up your App and then campaigns like Notifications, Coupons and Surveys. You can create variations
                based on user behavior (app opens), OS version, Internet connection, location and lot more. You can use
                notifications to intimate users about latest version release, give coupons to increase sales and conduct
                indepth surveys to get users' feedback on your product.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="step"><span class="step_2"></span>
              <p>Include our Android SDK in your application and then with couple of lines of code, you can easily 
                integrate it. Our SDK will show coupons on the fly as well as record user interaction details and send them
                to our dedicated servers. This integration is required only once and no changes are needed when you
                want to start/stop different types of campaigns.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="step"><span class="step_3"></span>
              <p>Put your mind at ease and deploy your app on few devices of your teammates and friends or, scale it
                to millions of users. In near real-time, you will be able to see detailed results and see your sales grow.
                Also, you can A/B test messages to see which one works best.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div><!-- id="web"   -->
      </div>
          </div>
